{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645796","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645796"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18134"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18134","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18134"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.77,0.05,0.05,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10848"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78404"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10848","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10848"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18134"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63766"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25242"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25245"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26869"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78404","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78404"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior compartment of the forearm is traversed by a number of arteries.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is typically found in this compartment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Superficial palmar arch","Anterior interosseous artery","Posterior interosseous artery","Posterior ulnar recurrent artery","Dorsal carpal arch"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior compartment of the forearm contains several important vascular structures. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior interosseous artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a major branch of the ulnar artery that runs in the anterior compartment of the forearm, along with the anterior interosseous nerve, supplying the deep flexor muscles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior interosseous artery\u003C/strong\u003E is found in the posterior compartment of the forearm, where it supplies the extensor muscles. It is not found in the anterior compartment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial palmar arch\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the palm of the hand, formed primarily by the ulnar artery. It is not found in the forearm compartments.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior ulnar recurrent artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a small branch that runs posteriorly around the elbow joint and is not typically considered part of the anterior compartment of the forearm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edorsal carpal arch\u003C/strong\u003E is located on the dorsal aspect of the hand and is not found in the forearm compartments.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the vascular anatomy of the forearm is crucial when assessing and managing forearm injuries, as damage to these vessels can lead to compromised blood supply to the muscles and other structures they supply.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anterior interosseous artery is a branch of the ulnar artery that supplies the anterior compartment of the forearm.","The anterior compartment of the forearm contains flexor muscles and is supplied by branches of the ulnar and radial arteries.","The posterior interosseous artery supplies the posterior compartment of the forearm."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences250."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63766"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18134"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63766","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63766"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T16:21:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T16:22:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10848"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78404"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.eme